Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mr. Pir Sayyed Ahmad Gaylani, the leader of the 
Mahaz-e Meli-ye Eslami-ye [National Islamic Front] of 
Afghanistan, met Foreign Affairs Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati 
this afternoon. He announced his party's stance on the civil 
war in Kabul and described the situation in Afghanistan as 
critical. 
  Mr. Gaylani also thanked the Islamic Republic of Iran for 
its 
efforts toward ending the war and establishing peace and 
stability in Afghanistan and the dispatch of humanitarian aid to 
the Muslim people of Afghanistan. 
  Mr. Velayati expressed concern about the situation in 
Afghanistan and said: The Islamic Republic of Iran will not 
spare any assistance that will bring peace and tranquillity to 
Afghanistan and end the clashes and war in that country. 

